The paper proposes a novel data augmentation technique for deep networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach is motivated by the semantic transformations in the deep feature space, which relates to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the cross-entropy loss and its robust variant, which are fundamental concepts in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed method can be applied to various datasets and tasks, which suggests the relevance to natural language processing (cs.CL).
